<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1488188" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?resize=600%2C314&#038;ssl=1" alt="RUGIPO announces Friday as resumption date" width="600" height="314" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?resize=300%2C157&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?resize=768%2C401&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?resize=58%2C30&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?resize=260%2C136&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?resize=200%2C105&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/RUGIPO.jpg?w=1020&amp;ssl=1 1020w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The management of Rufus Giwa Polytechnic, RUGIPO, Owo, Ondo State, on Wednesday asked its students to return to school on Friday, 6th November for the continuation of the first semester for 2019/2020 academic calendar after the COVID-19 lock-down break. This was disclosed in a statement by the Director, Public Relations and Protocol of the institution, Mr Samuel Ojo, in Owo. Ojo stated that the reopening was in line with the directive of the state government to ensure smooth continuous academic calendar of the institution. He said the first semester, which would commence immediately, was approved by the polytechnic’s board of studies having revised the 2019/2020 academic calendar. According to him, online matriculation of fresh students will take place in the first week of the resumption. The director explained that the first semester would come to an end by December 24, when the semester examinations would have been concluded. He added that the second semester of the 2019/2020 academic session will commence on January 3, 2021, while second-semester examinations for all categories of students would conclude on March 26, 2021. Ojo said that all students were expected to comply with the COVID-19 protocol to avoid the spread of the pandemic. “All students are to note that lectures will commence on Monday, 9th November 2020 and are also advised to adhere strictly to the COVID-19 protocols upon their resumption. “These will include maintenance of social distancing, regular hand washing and hand sanitising. “The students are to note that they are to come to the campus with their face masks and pocket-size hand sanitizers for their personal use. “The intent of the above is to intimate all the students for their compliance,” he said. Vanguard The University of Maiduguri on Wednesday denied media reports that it had extended its resumption date for both new and returning students by three months. August 9, 2012 In "News" The Student Union Government (SUG) of the Lagos State University (LASU), Ojo on Saturday commended the institution’s authorities for the new academic calendar approved by the senate of the institution. July 11, 2015 In "News" The management of Rufus Giwa Polytechnic, Owo (RUGIPO), Ondo State, on Tuesday, closed down the school over ASUP strike. June 18, 2019 In "News"